{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Parmesan cheese (optional) into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place pistachios, pine nuts, almonds and spices into mixing bowl and dry roast <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place cauliflower florets into mixing bowl and chop <b>2-3 sec\/\/speed 5<b>. Mix cauliflower with aid of spatula and repeat chopping, if necessary until an evenly chopped consistency is achieved. Transfer chopped cauliflower into Varoma dish and set aside.","Place garlic, spring onions\/shallots, 4 sprigs of the parsley and 4 sprigs of the coriander into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add mushrooms and wine and combine <b>10 sec\/\/speed 1<b>. Pour mushroom mixture over cauliflower in Varoma.","Place water into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket, then weigh sweet potato into it.","Place Varoma into position, then steam <b>15-18 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, or until sweet potato is cooked. Remove Varoma, then remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set vegetables aside to cool and drain for 5 minutes.","Place a large serving bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh currants and baby spinach into it.","Add dried apricots, reserved spice-nut mixture, cooled cauliflower-mushroom mixture and cooled sweet potato to serving bowl. Season to taste, then stir through remaining parsley and coriander leaves with spatula.","Serve immediately topped with reserved Parmesan cheese (optional) or cover and place in refrigerator until use."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into cubes (3 cm) (optional)","40 g shelled pistachios","40 g pine nuts","40 g slivered almonds","½ tsp ground cinnamon","½ tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground ginger","½ tsp ground coriander","½ tsp ground turmeric","700 - 750 g cauliflower, broken into florets (3 cm)","2 garlic cloves","4 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into quarters","8 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","8 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","200 g fresh mushrooms, cut into slices","30 g white wine","500 g water","300 g sweet potato, cut into pieces (1-2 cm)","50 g currants","80 g fresh baby spinach leaves, roughly chopped","12 dried apricots, cut into thin strips","½ tsp sea salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, to taste"]}],"id":"r83243","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Qv-5WpE5hT8\/XZWYpFYcIgI\/AAAAAAAAeBQ\/pLbRNb09PsAmyVxUN4LX04-xDb4miCr2ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Gj3uJYmgpdj64zJH.png","title":"Cauliflower rice pilaf with sweet potato","publishedAt":"2015-05-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19.3 g","fat":"22.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27.7 g","calories":"1721 kJ \/ 409 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large serving bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Serve cauliflower rice pilaf as a main course by it self or as a side dish. It makes a great salad to take to your next barbecue or picnic."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}